)\\n\\n#### Core Agent Interface\\nAll agents implement a common interface (`Agent`) with:\\n- `Bootstrap()` - One-time CI setup (auth config, warmup)\\n- `RunPrompt()` - Execute a single prompt and return output\\n- `StartSession()` - Interactive session management\\n- `IsTransientError()` - Detect retryable API failures\\n- `Name()`, `EntireAgent()` - Agent identification\\n\\n#### Claude Code Specific Implementation (`e2e/agents/claude.go`)\\n\\n**Bootstrap Phase (pre-test):**\\n```go\\nfunc (c *Claude) Bootstrap() error {\\n    // Only runs on CI (when CI env var is set)\\n    if os.Getenv(\\\"CI\\\") == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil  // Skip on local dev\\n    }\\n    \\n    apiKey := os.Getenv(\\\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\\\")\\n    if apiKey == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil  // Skip if no API key\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Write ~/.claude/.claude.json with API key config\\n    config := fmt.Sprintf(`{\\\"primaryApiKey\\\":%q,\\\"hasCompletedOnboarding\\\":true}`, apiKey)\\n    path := filepath.Join(home, \\\".claude\\\", \\\".claude.json\\\")\\n    return os.WriteFile(path, config, 0o644)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key points:**\\n- Only runs on CI when `CI` environment variable is set\\n- Reads `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` from environment\\n- Writes to `~/.claude/.claude.json` with the API key\\n- Sets `hasCompletedOnboarding: true` to skip onboarding dialogs\\n\\n### 2. **Authentication Strategies**\\n\\n#### On CI (GitHub Actions)\\n```\\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY (from GitHub secrets)\\n    ↓\\nBootstrap() writes to ~/.claude/.claude.json\\n    ↓\\nRunPrompt() uses isolated config dir (CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\\n    ↓\\nClaude Code reads API key from config file (not OAuth/Keychain)\\n```\\n\\n#### Locally (developer machine)\\n```\\nClaude Code relies on macOS Keychain or existing ~/.claude config\\n    ↓\\nBootstrap() skips (CI env var not set)\\n    ↓\\nRunPrompt() skips CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR override\\n    ↓\\nClaude Code uses default Keychain-based auth\\n```\\n\\n### 3. **Claude Code Invocation** (`RunPrompt` and `StartSession`)\\n\\n#### Non-Interactive Prompt (`RunPrompt`)\\nFile: `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/e2e/agents/claude.go:115-156`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (c *Claude) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n    // Create isolated config directory\\n    configDir, err := isolatedConfigDir()  // Temp dir mirroring ~/.claude\\n    defer os.RemoveAll(configDir)\\n    \\n    // Build command\\n    args := []string{\\\"-p\\\", prompt, \\\"--model\\\", \\\"haiku\\\", \\\"--dangerously-skip-permissions\\\"}\\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"claude\\\", args...)\\n    cmd.Dir = dir\\n    \\n    // Environment setup\\n    cmd.Env = append(cleanEnv(), \\n        \\\"ACCESSIBLE=1\\\",                    // Accessibility mode (no TUI)\\n        \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\",               // Not a TTY\\n        \\\"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\\\"+configDir)    // Isolated config (CI only)\\n    \\n    // Process management\\n    cmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{Setpgid: true}  // Process group\\n    cmd.Cancel = func() error {\\n        return syscall.Kill(-cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGKILL)  // Kill entire group on cancel\\n    }\\n    cmd.WaitDelay = 5 * time.Second  // Grace period after cancel\\n    \\n    // Run and capture output\\n    err = cmd.Run()\\n    return Output{Command, Stdout, Stderr, ExitCode}, err\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key environment variables:**\\n- `ACCESSIBLE=1` - Disables interactive TUI, uses simple text prompts\\n- `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` - Indicates not a real TTY (prevents ANSI escape sequences)\\n- `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` - Points to isolated config directory (CI only)\\n- `CLAUDECODE` is removed from environment (via `cleanEnv()`)\\n\\n**Invocation command:**\\n```bash\\nclaude -p \\\"<prompt>\\\" --model haiku --dangerously-skip-permissions\\n```\\n\\n#### Interactive Session (`StartSession`)\\nFile: `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/e2e/agents/claude.go:158-202`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (c *Claude) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n    name := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"claude-test-%d\\\", time.Now().UnixNano())\\n    \\n    envArgs := []string{\\\"ACCESSIBLE=1\\\", \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\"}\\n    if os.Getenv(\\\"CI\\\") != \\\"\\\" {\\n        // On CI: use isolated config dir\\n        configDir, err := isolatedConfigDir()\\n        if err == nil {\\n            envArgs = append(envArgs, \\\"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\\\"+configDir)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    // Locally: skip CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR so Keychain-based auth works\\n    \\n    // Launch via tmux with env variables\\n    args := append([]string{\\\"env\\\"}, envArgs...)\\n    args = append(args, \\\"claude\\\", \\\"--dangerously-skip-permissions\\\")\\n    \\n    s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"CLAUDECODE\\\"}, args[0], args[1:]...)\\n    \\n    // Dismiss startup dialogs until input prompt appears\\n    for range 5 {\\n        content, err := s.WaitFor(`❯`, 15*time.Second)  // Wait for Claude prompt\\n        // Handle permissions dialog with Down/Enter\\n        _ = s.SendKeys(\\\"Enter\\\")  // Dismiss dialog\\n    }\\n    return s, nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Tmux session creation:**\\n```bash\\ntmux new-session -d -s <name> -c <dir> \\\\\\n  env -u CLAUDECODE ACCESSIBLE=1 ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0 CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=... \\\\\\n  claude --dangerously-skip-permissions\\n```\\n\\n### 4. **Isolated Config Directory Pattern**\\n\\nFile: `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/e2e/agents/claude.go:15-43`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc isolatedConfigDir() (string, error) {\\n    home, _ := os.UserHomeDir()\\n    src := filepath.Join(home, \\\".claude\\\")\\n    \\n    // Create temp directory\\n    dst, _ := os.MkdirTemp(\\\"\\\", \\\"claude-config-*\\\")\\n    \\n    // Mirror ~/.claude contents via symlinks\\n    entries, _ := os.ReadDir(src)\\n    skip := map[string]bool{\\\"CLAUDE.md\\\": true, \\\"skills\\\": true}\\n    for _, e := range entries {\\n        if skip[e.Name()] {\\n            continue  // Skip personal instructions/skills\\n        }\\n        os.Symlink(filepath.Join(src, e.Name()), filepath.Join(dst, e.Name()))\\n    }\\n    return dst, nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Why isolated config:**\\n- Prevents test runs from inheriting personal `CLAUDE.md` instructions\\n- Prevents custom `skills/` from interfering with tests\\n- Allows API key injection via `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` override\\n- Cleaned up after prompt completes\\n\\n### 5. **Clean Environment Setup**\\n\\nFile: `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/e2e/agents/claude.go:45-55`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc cleanEnv() []string {\\n    var env []string\\n    for _, e := range os.Environ() {\\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(e, \\\"CLAUDECODE=\\\") {\\n            env = append(env, e)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    return env\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose:** Removes `CLAUDECODE` environment variable to prevent Claude Code from refusing to start inside the test runner.\\n\\n### 6. **E2E Test Execution Flow**\\n\\n#### File: `.github/workflows/e2e.yml`\\n\\n```yaml\\njobs:\\n  e2e-tests:\\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\\n    strategy:\\n      matrix:\\n        agent: [claude, opencode, gemini]\\n    \\n    steps:\\n      - name: Install agent CLI\\n        run: curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash\\n      \\n      - name: Bootstrap agent\\n        env:\\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\\n          GEMINI_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.GEMINI_API_KEY }}\\n        run: go run ./e2e/bootstrap  # Runs Bootstrap() for all agents\\n      \\n      - name: Run E2E Tests\\n        env:\\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\\n          GEMINI_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.GEMINI_API_KEY }}\\n        run: mise run test:e2e:${{ matrix.agent }}\\n```\\n\\n#### Test Execution: `e2e/tests/main_test.go`\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestMain(m *testing.M) {\\n    // Import agents to register them\\n    _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/e2e/agents\\\"  // Runs init() for each agent\\n    \\n    // Each agent's init() calls:\\n    // Register(&Claude{})  // R